dsiter.accessor

Class TypedUnaryOperator

  • java.lang.Object
    • dsiter.accessor.TypedUnaryOperator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IRowAccessor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NotOperator, SqrtOperator

    public abstract class TypedUnaryOperator
extends java.lang.Object
implements IRowAccessor
    Abstract class for use in creating unary operators. Not all unary operators need to use this class, but it's almost certainly easier to implement if you do.

    Subclasses must override the getReturnType(dsiter.row.ColumnType) and testTypeCompatibility(dsiter.row.ColumnType) methods. This class can then use that information to determine how best to process the source operator.

    This class provides overrideable methods for every possible type combination of source and returnValue (which means there are (# of types)^2 overridable methods available). Subclasses only need to override the methods which they will actually support. So, for example, a logical boolean operator only needs to override handle_boolean_boolean(boolean) and a numeric operator will only need to override the appropriate numeric handle_x_y method(s). This superclass will use the information from getReturnType(dsiter.row.ColumnType) and testTypeCompatibility(dsiter.row.ColumnType) to efficiently determine which method to call.
